<TrainingDetailsVTwo ID="x14925" Name="Content Full-Width" Layout="default-training_v2.xsl"><Title type="string" label="Title" readonly="false" hidden="false" required="true">Content Full-Width</Title><Abstract type="string" label="Abstract" readonly="false" hidden="false" required="true">Like the Content page, only without the left navigation.</Abstract><TrainingImage type="imagefile" label="Page Type Image" hidden="false" readonly="false" required="false" Expanded="true" AlternateText="" Border="" HSpace="" VSpace="" Width="300" Height="218" Alignment="">Internal_Use/Ingeniux_Training/Template Thumbnails/generalContentFullWidth.jpg</TrainingImage><BodyCopy type="dhtml" label="Body Copy" readonly="false" hidden="false" required="false"><![CDATA[<h3>Proper Use</h3>
<p>For the occasion where you need the full-width of the screen for content. For example, tables, very large images, flash objects, etc.</p>
<p>Please use this page type judiciously. Removing the left navigation will confuse some users. This page type differs from <a href="x14927.xml">Content with Return</a> in that it lacks the Return button. The only navigation for the user is the breadcrumb menu.</p>
<h3><img alt="Picture of breadcumb menus, a chain of menu links, with parent to the left of child, down to the current page." height="78" src="Images/Internal_Use/Ingeniux_Training/Breadcrumb menu.png" title="A sample breadcrumb menu" width="313" /></h3>
<p>Most of the time, the standard <a href="x14924.xml">Content</a> page should be used instead. <a href="x14927.xml">Content with Return</a> is the next best choice, with the Content Full-width being the least-favorable choice for your content.</p>
<h3>Audience</h3>
<p>This depends on you specific needs.</p>
<h3>Intended Authors</h3>
<p>All authors and editors.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
